        <h2>D, E, F</h2>
        <p>D-F graded diamonds make up the colorless family.  Sometimes dealers offer a bigger discount on these diamonds to offset the higher base. In those rare occasions, if the difference in price is not too steep compared to diamonds with lower color grades then by all means, you should grab the deal. Just make sure there isn’t another inferior characteristic that is causing the price to drop. </p>

